9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 734, L.D. 1864, “An Act to Facilitate the
10 Reconstruction of Storm-damaged Commercial Fisheries Facilities and Infrastructure”
11 Amend the bill in the emergency preamble in the 2nd paragraph in the last 2 lines (page
12 1, lines 6 and 7 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "town of Harpswell" and inserting
13 the following: 'State's coastal municipalities'
14 Amend the bill in the emergency preamble in the 3rd paragraph in the 2nd line (page
15 1, line 9 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "Harpswell" and inserting the following:
16 'the State'
17 Amend the bill in the emergency preamble in the 4th paragraph in the first line (page
18 1, line 12 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "local law" and inserting the following:
19 'certain local laws'
20 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and before the
21 emergency clause and inserting the following:
22 'Sec. 1. Variance petition; exemption from reasonable return variance
23 standard. The Maine Revised Statutes, Title 30-A, section 4353, subsection 4, paragraph
24 A does not apply to a petition for a variance from one or more provisions of a municipal
25 shoreland zoning ordinance or a municipal floodplain management ordinance that is filed
26 with the municipality's board of appeals established pursuant to Title 30-A, section 4353
27 if:
28 A. The petitioner demonstrates to the board of appeals that the petitioner suffered
29 substantial damage to a dock, pier or wharf, or a structure placed thereon, as a result of the
30 severe storms or flooding that occurred from January 9, 2024 to January 13, 2024;
31 B. The damaged dock, pier or wharf, or structure placed thereon, identified pursuant to
32 paragraph A is proposed to be reconstructed or replaced in kind and is a functionally water-
33 dependent structure or has a functionally water-dependent use; and
34 C. The petition is determined complete for processing by the board of appeals no later
35 than December 31, 2027.'
